      "content": "It is absolutely fair to say these regulations are counterproductive to a healthy economy right now because they prioritize abstract environmental goals over the immediate viability of working-class businesses. The narrative of \"growth vs. environment\" is a false dichotomy; a strong economy *requires* a stable, functioning small business sector. Instead of forcing compliance, the focus should be on policies that support industry while allowing for gradual, market-driven environmental improvements.",
